        <p>French physicist, astronomer, and politician. Professor of descriptive geometry at the École Polytechnique, 1809–30. Director of the Paris Observatory, where he gave public lectures on astronomy. An editor of the <hi rend="italic">Annales de chimie et physique</hi>, 1816–40. Permanent secretary of the Académie des Sciences, 1830. Foreign member, Royal Society, 1818.</p></note>
